# map.env — WHICH MISSION THE SERVER BOOTS. Runtime state, box-owned: the deploy seeds
# this file from map.env.example only when it is missing (fresh box / disaster recovery)
# and never overwrites it afterwards — edit it ON THE BOX and restart to switch maps
# (character saves follow, see prestart.sh).
#
# Valid values are mission directory names under mpmissions/ (dayzOffline.chernarusplus,
# dayzOffline.enoch, dayzOffline.sakhal, ...). This example is the ONE home of the
# default — prestart.sh re-seeds from map.env.example if map.env ever goes missing.
DAYZ_MISSION=dayzOffline.chernarusplus
